<subSubSection id="C3683DCCA744FFADFF5DF8C0368258C3" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A744FFADFF5DF8C0368258C3" blockId="29.[151,1437,1754,2033]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B906B255A744FFADFF5DF8C0353B5827" bold="true" box="[199,322,1861,1888]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This unique species is easily differentiated from all other species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7215C4A744FFADFBDEF8C330C95827" authority="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole, 2019" authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" box="[1092,1200,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B906B255A744FFADFBDEF8C330C95827" box="[1092,1200,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Afroptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its small size, the whitish body appearance and unstriped body (
<figureCitation id="134972C2A744FFADFD01F8EF369658C3" box="[667,751,1898,1924]" captionStart="FIGURE 43" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1735,1760]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,597,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[340,1247,597,1710]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 43. Afroptera alba Mansell &amp; Abdalla sp. nov., habitus. Forewing length = 22.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335134/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3683DCCA744FFAFFF5DF80834C65EE8" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A744FFADFF5DF808311C58B7" blockId="29.[151,1437,1754,2033]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B906B255A744FFADFF5DF808352058EF" bold="true" box="[199,345,1933,1960]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B906B255A744FFADFEC4F80A35F258EE" box="[350,395,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Size</emphasis>
(mm). Male: body length 8.9 (8.6–9.3); forewing 20.5 (20–21.6); hind wing 46.6 (43.8–48.4); antenna 14.3 (12.8–15.3). Female: body length 9.7 (8.5–11.4); forewing 21 (20–22.8); hind wing 42.3 (39.6–46.9); antenna 10.3 (9.4–11.5). 
<typeStatus id="54C9D0E5A744FFADFE35F853366E58B7" box="[431,535,2006,2032]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D74A5CEA744FFADFD84F852364F58B6" box="[542,566,2007,2033]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Body length 9.5; forewing 22.4; hind wing 48.1; antenna 15.3. (N = 10)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A747FFAEFF5DFF1C35895E58" blockId="30.[151,1436,153,539]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B906B255A747FFAEFF5DFF1C357D5FF4" box="[199,260,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Head</emphasis>
. Frons, clypeus light yellow. Genae and maxilla creamy white. Palpi light brown. Vertex light yellowish brown. Eyes small, black, widely separated. Antennae short, not reaching pterostigma, whitish yellow proximally, darkish brown distally with black setae. Terminal segment mainly membranous and approximately same length as penultimate segment (
<figureCitation id="134972C2A747FFAEFE15FE80359A5E58" box="[399,483,260,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–66" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1562,1587]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,237,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[227,1361,227,1505]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 56–66.Antennae of Afroptera spp. 56, A. acuta sp. nov.; 57, A. alba sp. nov.; 58, A. koranna sp. nov.; 59, A. folia sp. nov.; 60, A. cylindrata sp. nov.; 61, A. balli sp. nov.; 62, A. maraisi sp. nov.; 63, A. apicalis (Tjeder); 64, A. bitis (Tjeder); 65, A. aequabilis (Tjeder); 66, A. brinkmani sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335142/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A747FFAEFF5DFEAC35F55D5C" blockId="30.[151,1436,153,539]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="B906B255A747FFAEFF5DFEAC35595E04" box="[199,288,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Thorax.</emphasis>
White, heavily powdered, without distinct longitudinal mid and lateral stripes (
<figureCitation id="134972C2A747FFAEFB03FEAC30945E04" box="[1177,1261,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–49" captionStartId="35.[151,262,1120,1145]" captionTargetBox="[249,1337,277,1085]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[249,1338,277,1085]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 46–49. Thorax of Afroptera spp. 46, A. folia sp. nov; 47, A. acuta sp. nov; 48, A. alba sp. nov; 49, A. balli sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335136/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). Fore and hind margins of pronotum with long white hairs and no black hairs. Sparse smooth white hairs present behind anterior hairs on fore margin. Distal lateral sides also with long white hairs. Whole mesonotum with white pubescence, markedly longer and denser on antero-lateral portions and on disc of prescutum than mesoscutum and mesoscutellum. Sides of mesoscutum naked except for a few short white hairs posteriorly on each side. Two tufts of long white hairs also present laterally on hind margin of the mesocutllum. Metanotum with two groups of long white hairs laterally on each side.
</paragraph>
