<subSubSection id="C3683DCCA746FFAFFF5DFDA1372C5DEC" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD6E47A746FFAFFF5DFDA1372C5DEC" blockId="31.[151,1437,153,683]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B906B255A746FFAFFF5DFDA1358B5D78" bold="true" box="[199,498,548,575]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7215C4A746FFAFFE63FDA036E75D78" authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" box="[505,670,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B906B255A746FFAFFE63FDA036E75D78" box="[505,670,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Afroptera alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3652ED7A746FFAFFCD8FDA037DB5D78" box="[834,930,549,575]" name="Namibia" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Namibia</collectingCountry>
where its distribution is in the Namib Desert Eco-region (
<figureCitation id="134972C2A746FFAFFEB9FDCC35FF5D24" box="[291,390,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 153–154" captionStartId="71.[151,264,1983,2008]" captionTargetBox="[174,1414,179,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[174,1414,179,1955]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURES 153–154. Distribution maps of Afroptera spp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335180/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 154</figureCitation>
). The collection site is in the Namib Desert west of the Great Escarpment. The area is mostly gravel plains, sand dunes and scattered mountain outcrops, vegetated mostly by grasses, shrubs, and ephemeral plants near the escarpment with sparse trees (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE313B6A746FFAFFD0BFD1437305DEC" author="Nicholson, S. E." box="[657,841,657,683]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="385 - 388" refId="ref48942" refString="Nicholson, S. E. (2011) Dryland Climatology. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, pp. 4 pp. [pp. 385 - 388] https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / CBO 9780511973840" type="book chapter" year="2011">Nicholson 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
